Launch Chameleon – On This Day application in Windows 8.1, you can see this application setting pane in left and a preview of “On This Day” embedded in your current LockScreen background.



Setting pane introduction:

  • Reload: Refresh current preview in application, reload your current LockScreen background and read current day data from WikiPedia.org. Generate one preview in application.

  • See More: Launch web browser to WikiPedia.org, you could see more about this day events in history.

  • Set LockScreen: Set current preview image as your current device LockScreen background.

  • Start: Setup a background task in system and can automatically update your LockScreen background in every 15 minutes.

  • Stop: Stop the background task in system to update the LockScreen background.

  • Help: Launch help page in web browser.

  • About: Show the information this application.



Q&A: How to change the position of “On This Day” region in background image?

Use your finger or mouse on the drag handler and move, now you could drag the region to any place you like to show the “On This Day”. Then release your finger or mouse.
